<DocsLayout title="Features Overview - Yako Docs" description="A complete overview of Yako's features.">
  <h1>Features Overview</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Everything Yako has to offer.</p>

  <h2>Views</h2>
  <p>Yako offers three distinct views you can switch between in Settings:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Classic</strong> — A clean new tab page with backgrounds, clock, quick links, and more.</li>
    <li><strong>MSPortals.io</strong> — A searchable directory of Microsoft admin portals, sourced from the <a href="https://msportals.io" rel="noreferrer noopener">MSPortals.io</a> community project.</li>
    <li><strong>cmd.ms</strong> — A command-line style interface to quickly jump to any Microsoft admin portal using <a href="https://cmd.ms" rel="noreferrer noopener">cmd.ms</a> shortcuts.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Portal Search</h2>
  <p>
    The integrated search bar provides instant suggestions from a catalog of 900+ Microsoft portals sourced from
    <a href="https://cmd.ms" rel="noreferrer noopener">cmd.ms</a> and
    <a href="https://msportals.io" rel="noreferrer noopener">MSPortals.io</a>.
    Find any portal by name, URL, or category. Results appear as you type — just press Enter or click to open.
  </p>

  <h2>Quick Links</h2>
  <p>
    Quick Links give you one-click access to your most-used portals. By default, Yako comes pre-configured with
    popular Microsoft portals including Entra, Intune, M365 Admin Center, Azure, and Defender.
  </p>
  <p>You can:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Add links manually or from the built-in portal catalog</li>
    <li>Organize links into groups and pages</li>
    <li>Choose from multiple display styles: large, medium, small, inline, or text</li>
    <li>Rearrange links by dragging</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Clock & Date</h2>
  <p>
    A clean clock display with multiple options:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Digital or analog display</li>
    <li>Show seconds, 12/24 hour format</li>
    <li>Multiple analog clock face styles</li>
    <li>World clocks for multiple time zones</li>
    <li>Customizable date format</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Greetings</h2>
  <p>
    Set your name and Yako will greet you with a personalized message that changes throughout the day —
    Good morning, Good afternoon, Good evening.
  </p>

  <h2>Backgrounds</h2>
  <p>
    Customize your new tab background with:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Solid colors</li>
    <li>Local images from your computer</li>
    <li>Local videos</li>
    <li>Background blur and brightness controls</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Notes</h2>
  <p>
    A built-in notes widget that supports basic Markdown, including headings, lists, and checkboxes.
    Always accessible from your new tab.
  </p>

  <h2>Dark Mode</h2>
  <p>
    Yako supports automatic dark mode that follows your system preference. You can also set it
    to always on, always off, or switch based on time of day.
  </p>

  <h2>Custom CSS</h2>
  <p>
    For advanced customization, Yako includes a built-in CSS editor with syntax highlighting.
    Change fonts, colors, spacing, layouts — the full extension UI is yours to customize.
    See the <a href="/docs/styles/">CSS Snippets</a> page for ready-made examples.
  </p>

  <h2>Page Layout</h2>
  <p>
    Control how widgets are arranged on the page. Adjust the page width, gap between elements,
    and rearrange widgets using the layout editor.
  </p>

  <h2>Settings Management</h2>
  <p>
    Export and import your settings as a JSON file. Transfer your configuration between browsers
    or share it with others.
  </p>

  <h2>Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Yako only requires the <code>storage</code> permission. It collects no data,
    has no account system, and relies on no third-party services.
    Portal data is fetched from GitHub to stay up to date, but no personal information is sent.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
